00:20:14,421 --> 00:20:16,724
MMM.
HOW MANY TOTAL STORES
ARE YOU ACTUALLY IN?

00:20:16,724 --> 00:20:18,358
ABOUT 650.

00:20:18,358 --> 00:20:20,861
SO WHAT DO YOU NEED
THE MONEY FOR?

00:20:20,861 --> 00:20:23,363
WE NEED THE MONEY
TO HELP US WITH PRODUCTION.

00:20:23,363 --> 00:20:25,866
I CURRENTLY HAVE OVER $100,000
WORTH OF ORDERS

00:20:25,866 --> 00:20:28,368
THAT OUR CUSTOMERS
ARE EAGERLY WAITING FOR.

00:20:28,368 --> 00:20:32,072
YOU CAN'T GET FINANCING
FROM A BANK OR SOMEBODY ELSE?

00:20:32,072 --> 00:20:33,640
IT'S PRETTY DIFFICULT
RIGHT NOW.

00:20:33,640 --> 00:20:35,976
EVEN A LOT OF
THE ANGEL INVESTORS

00:20:35,976 --> 00:20:37,945
THAT ARE USUALLY AVAILABLE
IN THIS MARKET

00:20:37,945 --> 00:20:40,180
HAVE BEEN
PRETTY DIFFICULT TO REACH.
THAT'S THE REAL PROBLEM

00:20:40,180 --> 00:20:42,616
WITH WHAT'S HAPPENING
IN AMERICA TODAY

00:20:42,616 --> 00:20:45,886
IS PEOPLE CAN'T GET CREDIT.
RIGHT, RIGHT.

00:20:45,886 --> 00:20:47,988
DESERVING PEOPLE WITH
REAL BUSINESSES AND REAL ORDERS

00:20:47,988 --> 00:20:49,990
CAN'T GET CREDIT.
MY CONCERN IS,

00:20:49,990 --> 00:20:51,959
IS THAT YOU'RE NOT MAKING,
REALLY, MUCH PROFIT.

00:20:51,959 --> 00:20:55,596
2% PROFIT ON $700,000--
THAT'S PROJECTED FOR THIS YEAR.

00:20:55,596 --> 00:20:58,065
THAT'S A $15,000 PROFIT.

00:20:58,065 --> 00:21:00,067
DON'T YOU THINK
WHAT YOU'RE ASKING

00:21:00,067 --> 00:21:02,202
AND VALUING YOUR COMPANY FOR
IS TOO HIGH?

00:21:02,202 --> 00:21:05,806
I PERSONALLY HAVE OVER $800,000
INVESTED IN THIS.

00:21:05,806 --> 00:21:09,376
SUSAN, DON'T CARE ABOUT
THE PAST. DOESN'T MATTER.

00:21:09,376 --> 00:21:11,512
OKAY,
EVERYBODY LOVES YOUR STUFF.

00:21:11,512 --> 00:21:14,848
YOUR PACKAGING'S FANTASTIC.
YOU PRESENT VERY, VERY WELL.

00:21:14,848 --> 00:21:20,020
PUT THAT ASIDE.
LET'S TALK ABOUT THE MONEY.

00:21:20,020 --> 00:21:23,924
WE HAVE TO TAKE THE EMOTION
OUT OF IT AND MAKE IT REAL.

00:21:23,924 --> 00:21:25,859
HOW ABOUT THIS DEAL?

00:21:25,859 --> 00:21:29,096
500K...

00:21:29,096 --> 00:21:32,065
AND YOU GIVE UP 70%
OF YOUR COMPANY.

00:21:32,065 --> 00:21:34,735
ARE YOU ASKING ME
IF I WOULD ACCEPT THAT?

00:21:34,735 --> 00:21:35,869
YES.

00:21:35,869 --> 00:21:38,505
NO, THANK YOU.

00:21:38,505 --> 00:21:42,442
OKAY, I HAVE $500,000...

00:21:42,442 --> 00:21:45,145
FOR 51%.

00:21:45,145 --> 00:21:47,614
51%?

00:21:47,614 --> 00:21:50,951
51% TO ME.
I CONTROL THE COMPANY.

00:21:52,719 --> 00:21:54,288
I'D GO 50%.

00:21:54,288 --> 00:21:57,090
HALF A MILLION FOR 50%.

00:21:58,659 --> 00:22:00,727
I'D GO IN ON THAT DEAL.

00:22:00,727 --> 00:22:03,230
I THINK 50 IS FAIR,
BECAUSE AT THE END OF THE DAY,

00:22:03,230 --> 00:22:04,731
YOU NEED THE MONEY,

00:22:04,731 --> 00:22:07,201
WE GOTTA HAVE
SOME LEVEL OF CONTROL.

00:22:07,201 --> 00:22:11,038
SO I'M IN WITH KEVIN
ON THAT DEAL.

00:22:11,038 --> 00:22:14,241
DO WE HAVE A DEAL?
WELL, LET'S SEE--

00:22:14,241 --> 00:22:15,742
SUSAN, LET'S BE CLEAR.

00:22:15,742 --> 00:22:19,079
KEVIN AND I ARE OFFERING YOU
$500,000

00:22:19,079 --> 00:22:20,914
FOR 50% OF THE COMPANY.

00:22:20,914 --> 00:22:24,318
WHY DEAL WITH TWO GUYS WHEN YOU
COULD JUST DEAL WITH ONE

00:22:24,318 --> 00:22:27,955
FOR 51%?
I WOULDN'T THROW OUT THE 70%
THAT LEAVES YOU WITH 30,

00:22:27,955 --> 00:22:31,124
'CAUSE YOU GET TO WORK
WITH MR. WONDERFUL. THAT'S ME.
(laughs)

00:22:31,124 --> 00:22:33,694
(laughs)
SUSAN, WE HAVE--
YOU HAVE AN OFFER.

00:22:35,162 --> 00:22:38,398
WHAT DO YOU WANT TO DO?

00:22:38,398 --> 00:22:40,100
(exhales deeply)

00:22:40,100 --> 00:22:43,103
YOU WANT TO GO IN THE DARK
AND THINK ABOUT IT?
FOR JUST A SECOND?

00:22:43,103 --> 00:22:46,406
(Daymond) YOU WANT TO
STEP OUT ONE SECOND?
YEAH, GO AHEAD. PHONE
YOUR HUSBAND IF YOU HAVE TO.

00:22:46,406 --> 00:22:49,509
DOES HE OWN
ANY OF THE BUSINESS?
NO.

00:22:49,509 --> 00:22:51,178
(Barbara laughs)
(Harrington) HE JUST PUT
ALL THE MONEY IN.

00:22:51,178 --> 00:22:53,947
OOH, THAT'S MEAN.
I LIKE HER EVEN MORE NOW.

00:22:53,947 --> 00:22:56,450
FIRST OF ALL,
WHAT IS THIS 50% STUFF?

00:22:56,450 --> 00:22:58,185
WE CAN GET 70% HERE.

00:22:58,185 --> 00:23:00,287
EASILY. WE CAN GET 80%.

00:23:00,287 --> 00:23:02,689
SHE SAID NO.
SHE SAID NO TO YOUR 70%.
(Harrington)
SHE TURNED YOU DOWN.

00:23:02,689 --> 00:23:04,691
YEAH, BUT, YOU KNOW,
I HAVE 51.

00:23:04,691 --> 00:23:06,727
YOU GUYS ARE TAKING MY DEAL,
ALMOST, FOR 1 POINT.

00:23:06,727 --> 00:23:08,896
NO, BUT YOU GUYS, YOU UNDERCUT
ME BY GOING DOWN TO 50--

00:23:08,896 --> 00:23:11,431
AND THEY UNDERCUT ME.
YEAH, THEY UNDERCUT HIM.
IT'S ALL FAIR. COME ON.

00:23:11,431 --> 00:23:14,468
SHE WASN'T GONNA--
SHE'S NOT GONNA TAKE THAT.

00:23:14,468 --> 00:23:17,404
(O'Leary) ALL RIGHT.
LET'S GET HER BACK.
SUSAN, YOU WANT TO COME BACK.

00:23:17,404 --> 00:23:20,440
♪♪

00:23:24,144 --> 00:23:26,713
WHAT DO YOU WANT TO DO?

00:23:26,713 --> 00:23:28,749
♪♪

00:23:40,687 --> 00:23:43,156
SUSAN HAS TWO OFFERS
ON THE TABLE,

00:23:43,156 --> 00:23:45,887
BOTH ASKING FOR A BIGGER CHUNK
OF HER COMPANY.

00:23:45,887 --> 00:23:48,956
I LOVE THE FACT THAT
YOU'VE GOT $700,000 IN SALES,

00:23:48,956 --> 00:23:51,959
YOU'VE GOT $100,000 IN ORDERS
WAITING TO BE FULFILLED.

00:23:51,959 --> 00:23:54,228
I LOVE THAT, OKAY?

00:23:54,228 --> 00:23:56,631
MY OFFER
WITH ROBERT AS MY PARTNER--

00:23:56,631 --> 00:23:58,933
WE'LL EACH--
TOGETHER PUT UP $500,000

00:23:58,933 --> 00:24:00,768
FOR 50% OF THE COMPANY.

00:24:00,768 --> 00:24:03,838
MY OFFER IS...

00:24:03,838 --> 00:24:07,308
I WILL GIVE YOU $500,000

00:24:07,308 --> 00:24:09,310
FOR 51%.

00:24:09,310 --> 00:24:11,579
THAT GIVES ME
CONTROLLING INTEREST,

00:24:11,579 --> 00:24:15,616
BUT YOU ONLY HAVE TO DEAL WITH
ONE PERSON INSTEAD OF TWO.

00:24:15,616 --> 00:24:18,586
(laughs)
YOU'RE ALL WONDERFUL.

00:24:18,586 --> 00:24:21,889
NOW HERE'S WHAT I WOULD LIKE
TO PROPOSE TO YOU TWO GENTLEMEN

00:24:21,889 --> 00:24:25,026
OR TO YOU.

00:24:25,026 --> 00:24:28,996
WOULD YOU CONSIDER 49/51 SO I
MAINTAIN 51% OF THE COMPANY?

00:24:28,996 --> 00:24:30,932
CAN'T DO THAT.

00:24:30,932 --> 00:24:32,934
I DON'T WANT TO SPEAK
FOR KEVIN HARRINGTON,

00:24:32,934 --> 00:24:34,936
BUT I CAN'T DO THAT.
NO.

00:24:34,936 --> 00:24:37,872
AND I'LL TELL YOU WHY
I CAN'T DO THAT.
OKAY.

00:24:37,872 --> 00:24:39,874
IN A SMALL BUSINESS,
THE DECISIONS YOU MAKE

00:24:39,874 --> 00:24:42,276
CAN REALLY INFLUENCE
WHICH WAY WE'RE GONNA GO.

00:24:42,276 --> 00:24:45,346
AND I JUST NEED TO BE INVOLVED.
BUT ALONG WITH KEVIN HARRINGTON,

00:24:45,346 --> 00:24:48,149
I'M WILLING TO GO WITH YOU
'CAUSE I LIKE YOU.

00:24:48,149 --> 00:24:50,151
SO I'M WILLING
TO SHARE RESPONSIBILITY,

00:24:50,151 --> 00:24:53,788
BUT I'M NOT WILLING TO GIVE YOU
THAT RESPONSIBILITY.
OKAY.

00:24:53,788 --> 00:24:56,557
I-I HAVE TO CONTROL MY MONEY.
YOU'VE SPOKEN FOR ME
VERY WELL. THANK YOU, ROBERT.

00:24:56,557 --> 00:24:58,893
(Daymond)
YOU HAVE NOT GIVEN ME AN ANSWER.

00:24:58,893 --> 00:25:02,163
CAN I HAVE CONTROLLING STAKE
OF YOUR COMPANY FOR 51%?

00:25:05,232 --> 00:25:06,801
(blows air)

00:25:06,801 --> 00:25:08,803
DO YOU KNOW, I HATE TO SAY IT?

00:25:08,803 --> 00:25:10,571
BUT, UM...

00:25:10,571 --> 00:25:12,473
BUT NO.

00:25:12,473 --> 00:25:14,875
AND--AND THANK YOU
VERY MUCH.
THEN I'M OUT.

00:25:14,875 --> 00:25:18,879
ARE YOU SAYING NO TO DAYMOND
OR ARE YOU SAYING--
I'M SAYING NO TO DAYMOND.

00:25:18,879 --> 00:25:23,017
AND YOU TWO GENTLEMEN,
I'M, UM...

00:25:23,017 --> 00:25:25,620
(O'Leary) SUSAN,
THINK ABOUT THIS.

00:25:25,620 --> 00:25:27,755
YOU MAKE NO MONEY.

00:25:29,890 --> 00:25:31,792
I WILL--OH, GOSH.

00:25:34,195 --> 00:25:37,064
I-I WILL SAY YES TO.

00:25:37,064 --> 00:25:38,466
YES.
(Barbara) HEY.

00:25:38,466 --> 00:25:40,701
GOOD CHOICE.
AHA. AHA.

00:25:40,701 --> 00:25:42,970
SHE'S GONNA SAY NO,
HUH, DAYMOND?
YOU TOOK ME FOR 1%.

00:25:42,970 --> 00:25:45,773
SHE'S GONNA SAY NO, HUH?
SHE'S GONNA REGRET IT.

00:25:45,773 --> 00:25:48,275
AH. SUSAN, YOU MADE
THE RIGHT DECISION.

00:25:48,275 --> 00:25:50,544
WELL, AND HE LOVES
THE PRODUCT ALREADY.

00:25:50,544 --> 00:25:51,879
CONGRATULATIONS.
OUTSTANDING.

00:25:51,879 --> 00:25:54,515
THANK YOU.
GOOD MATCH.

00:25:54,515 --> 00:25:56,917
(Daymond) THAT IS A--
THAT IS A GOOD DEAL.

00:25:56,917 --> 00:25:59,253
THAT IS A GREAT LADY.
GREAT LADY.

00:25:59,253 --> 00:26:01,622
(Robert) THAT IS
A GOOD LADY.
AH! I SHOULDA GOT IN
ON YOUR DEAL.

00:26:01,622 --> 00:26:05,126
IT FEELS A LITTLE BIT SCARY
TO GIVE UP 50% OF MY COMPANY.

00:26:05,126 --> 00:26:07,895
BUT KNOWING THAT MY INTENT

00:26:07,895 --> 00:26:10,865
IS TO HAVE THIS BE
A $20-MILLION COMPANY

00:26:10,865 --> 00:26:12,633
OVER THE NEXT FIVE YEARS,

00:26:12,633 --> 00:26:15,870
WHAT'S 50%?

